NEWS & STORIES — Cover Images
==============================

One cover image per article. These appear as thumbnails on the /news/ listing page
and as the header image on individual article pages.

SIZE:     1200 × 675 px  (16:9 ratio)
FORMAT:   JPG

NAMING CONVENTION
-----------------
Name each file after the article's slug (the URL segment).
Examples:
  fab-lab-opening.jpg
  hydrogen-village-launch.jpg
  bali-fab-fest-2024-recap.jpg

To find an article's slug, look at its URL:
  meaningful-design.org/news/fab-lab-opening/  →  fab-lab-opening.jpg

NOTES
-----
- If you're not sure of the slug, use a descriptive name and let Claude know
  which article each image belongs to.
- A single strong, well-composed photo per article is enough.
- Avoid text overlaid on the photo — the site will add the title itself.
